A Taita Taveta education officer has warned students against having phones in school, saying he will crash them if found. Voi DEO Kennedy Machora said parents of form four students will not be allowed to visit their children until the Kenya National Certificate of Secondary examinations are completed.He spoke at Voi Secondary School during the launch of the Global e-School Communities Initiative and African Digital Schools Initiative Kenya.Machora said students use phones to cheat in exams while some parents visit their children to give them exam leakage.He urged parents whose children have phones in school that the phones will be crashed, regardless of their value. The digital programme will benefit 20 schools in the county. It will run for the next five years. It aims to increase digital literacy among students and teachers.